title: Horseback archery takes speed, precision, and stability #Superskilled

author: National Geographic
description:
In the vast grassy plains of Mongolia, a country defined by epic landscapes and ancient horse culture, Eva zu Beck sets out on a mission to become a modern-day warrior, guided by a female horseback archery champion. Join Eva as she learns the fundamentals of archery and how to combine it with hands-free horseback riding. Along the way, she connects with local nomadic communities, witnesses the timeless traditions, and gains a deeper understanding of one of the world's best-preserved ancient cultures and what it takes to keep these traditions alive in the modern world.
